Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in\mathcal{S}_{n}^{+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $B\in\mathcal{S}_{n}^{+}$
\end_inset

 be positive definite matrices so that 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is a 
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa-$
\end_inset

approximation of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
A\preceq B\preceq\kappa A\label{eq:A-B-bounds}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

Given 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta\in\left(0,1\right)$
\end_inset

, the algorithm 
\family typewriter
PreconditionedLogDetMonteCarlo
\family default
 computes 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{n}\log\left|B^{-1}A\right|$
\end_inset

 up to precision 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 with probability greater than 
\begin_inset Formula $1-\eta$
\end_inset

, by performing 
\begin_inset Formula $16\kappa\left(\frac{1}{\epsilon}+\frac{1}{n\epsilon^{2}}\right)\log\left(\frac{2\kappa}{\epsilon}\right)\log\left(2/\eta\right)\log^{2}\left(\kappa\right)$
\end_inset

 vector inversions from 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 and vector multiplies from 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

. 
